cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with video streaming over cellular networks and proposes a solution to address the issues caused by unreliable wireless channels. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a likely category as the paper focuses on improving the quality of video streaming. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) could be a relevant category as the paper proposes an algorithm for anticipatory download scheduling. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) could be a relevant category as the paper deals with optimizing the download scheduling to avoid buffer underruns and over-buffering. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) could also be a relevant category as the paper deals with anticipating future data rates to optimize the download scheduling.
